\title{Pr Creator}

\taxon{skill}

\subtree{
\title{Pull Request Creator}
\p{This skill guides the creation of high-quality Pull Requests that adhere to the repository's standards.}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\p{Follow these steps to create a Pull Request:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Branch Management}: Check the current branch to avoid working directly}
\li{Run \code{\startverb git branch --show-current\stopverb}.}
\li{If the current branch is \code{\startverb main\stopverb}, create and switch to a new descriptive}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Locate Template}: Search for a pull request template in the repository.}
\li{Check \code{\startverb .github/pull_request_template.md\stopverb}}
\li{Check \code{\startverb .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md\stopverb}}
\li{If multiple templates exist (e.g., in \code{\startverb .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/\stopverb}),}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Read Template}: Read the content of the identified template file.}
}

